# ⚠️ S44 PROTECTIONS:
# - Button variant NAMES (glass, glass-strong, glass-glow, glass-subtle, glass-outline) — DO NOT RENAME
# - GlassButton is SEPARATE from Button — DO NOT MERGE
# - GlassCard / GlassInputWrapper APIs unchanged
# - glass-glow::before with inset: -14px MUST keep overflow: visible
# - glass-input animation (4s pulse) must still work on idle
# - data-state="error"/"success" API on inputs preserved
# - contain: layout style paint on .glass surfaces — KEEP
# You MAY change height values (h-10→h-11 etc) but NOT variant names or CSS class names.

###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Update all UI and app-level components to enforce 44px+ touch targets.
Use tokens from T2. NO ad-hoc pixel values.

###############################################################################
# COMPONENTS TO UPDATE
###############################################################################

### 1. button.tsx — Size variants
Update size default values per T2 mapping.
Ensure all variants that produce interactive elements are ≥ 44px.
Key: `default` → h-12, `sm` → h-11, `icon` → h-11 w-11.

### 2. input.tsx — Default height
Set default height to h-12 (48px).
Ensure glass-input variant is h-12.
Search input variant: h-12.

### 3. switch.tsx — Touch area
Radix Switch visual size may be small.
Wrap with touch-area utility or increase overall size.
Minimum interactive area: 44x44px.

### 4. theme-toggle.tsx — CRITICAL FIX
Current: h-8 w-8 (32px) — 12px below minimum!
Fix: h-11 w-11 (44px) minimum.
Keep icon size the same (h-4 w-4), increase button area.

### 5. mobile-shell.tsx — Bottom nav tabs
Current: py-2 pt-2.5 (approximately 40px).
Fix: add min-h-[56px] or use --nav-item-h token.
Each tab button must be ≥ 44px touch target.
Icon size stays h-5 w-5; touch area increases.

### 6. mobile-header.tsx — Back button
Current: implicit sizing from content.
Fix: ensure back button area is ≥ 44x44px.
Header height: h-12 → OK (48px), keep as is.

### 7. bottom-select-modal.tsx — List items
Current: no explicit min-height for selectable items.
Fix: add min-h-[48px] or min-h-[3rem] to each list item.
Cancel button: ensure ≥ 44px.

### 8. date-range-picker.tsx — Calendar cells & time slider
Calendar day cells: ensure ≥ 44x44px tap target.
Time slider: ensure touch-friendly height.
Done/Cancel buttons: ≥ 44px.

### 9. glass-button.tsx, glass-card.tsx, glass-input-wrapper.tsx
Verify all sizes meet 44px minimum for interactive variants.
GlassButton: ensure smallest variant is ≥ 44px.
GlassInputWrapper: input height 48px.

### 10. select.tsx — Trigger sizing
Select trigger: ensure ≥ 48px height.
Select items in dropdown: ensure ≥ 44px per item.

###############################################################################
# SPECIAL: RANGE SLIDERS
###############################################################################
Range inputs (tracking-screen.tsx, object-details-screen.tsx):
- Track height: h-2 (8px) — visually fine
- BUT thumb (the draggable circle) must be ≥ 44px
- Add CSS for input[type=range]:
  ```css
  input[type="range"] {
    min-height: var(--touch-min);
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    width: 24px;
    height: 24px;
    /* With padding, total touch area ≥ 44px */
  }
  ```

###############################################################################
# SPECIAL: CHECKBOXES (select-objects-screen.tsx)
###############################################################################
Current: h-7 w-7 (28px) visual checkbox circles.
Fix options:
  A) Increase visual size to h-11 w-11 (44px) — may look too large
  B) Keep visual h-7 w-7 but add .touch-area to extend hit area
  C) Make the entire row tappable (already is — the row button handles it)
Recommended: Option C — the row itself is a button. The checkbox is purely
visual. Verify the row has min-h-[56px] and is the actual touch target.

###############################################################################
# RULES (from DESIGN_SPRINT_GUIDE.md lessons)
###############################################################################
rules:
  - Use tokens, not ad-hoc values: var(--touch-target) not h-12
  - Update the COMPONENT, not each screen usage: ButtonProps default size
    handles all instances automatically
  - Test build after each component update — don't batch all changes
  - If a visual element must stay small, use .touch-area for the hit area

###############################################################################
# ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
###############################################################################
verify:
  - [ ] button.tsx: all size variants ≥ 44px
  - [ ] input.tsx: default height = 48px
  - [ ] switch.tsx: touch area ≥ 44x44px
  - [ ] theme-toggle.tsx: h-11 w-11 (44px)
  - [ ] mobile-shell.tsx: nav items ≥ 44px, spacing ≥ 8px
  - [ ] bottom-select-modal.tsx: list items min-h 48px
  - [ ] date-range-picker.tsx: calendar cells ≥ 44px, buttons ≥ 44px
  - [ ] range sliders: thumb ≥ 24px, total touch area adequate
  - [ ] select-objects checkboxes: tap area ≥ 44px (via row or touch-area)
  - [ ] pnpm run build passes with zero errors
